@startuml gateway-coexistence
' Two conformant Gateway API controllers (Traefik + Istio) coexisting on one
' cluster: distinct GatewayClasses and entry addresses, the SAME backend
' Services. Illustrates docs/gateway-api-ingress.md "Running more than one
' controller". Rendered by `make diagrams`.
skinparam backgroundColor #FAFAFA
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam roundCorner 8
skinparam defaultFontName "Inter, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif"
skinparam defaultFontSize 13
skinparam ArrowColor #475569
skinparam ArrowFontColor #475569
skinparam rectangle {
  BorderColor #1E3A8A
  BackgroundColor #2563EB
  FontColor #FFFFFF
  BorderThickness 1
}
skinparam NoteBackgroundColor #F1F5F9
skinparam NoteBorderColor #94A3B8

title Two Gateway API controllers, one set of backends — Traefik + Istio coexisting

' --- distinct entry addresses (no collision) ---
rectangle "client → **host :80 / :443**\nkind hostPort (localhost)" as hp #0F766E
rectangle "client → **LB IP**\ncloud-provider-kind (per-Service)" as lb #0F766E

' --- controllers: distinct controllerName, so no API-level conflict ---
rectangle "**Traefik**\nGatewayClass: traefik\ncontrollerName: traefik.io/gateway-controller\n(existing Traefik pod — no extra workload)" as traefik
rectangle "**Istio**\nGatewayClass: istio\ncontrollerName: istio.io/gateway-controller\n(auto-provisioned Envoy Service: istio-istio)" as istio

' --- routes: parentRef picks the Gateway, backendRefs the Services ---
rectangle "HTTPRoute\nparentRef → traefik" as rt_t #3B82F6
rectangle "HTTPRoute\nparentRef → istio" as rt_i #3B82F6

' --- one shared backend set: both routes' backendRefs converge here ---
rectangle "**Shared backend Services**\nhelloweb · golang-web · foo-service\n(identical pods — one set)" as backends #0F766E

hp --> traefik
lb --> istio
traefik --> rt_t
istio --> rt_i
rt_t --> backends : backendRefs
rt_i --> backends : backendRefs

note bottom of backends
  Same pods, two front doors. Each controller reconciles only Gateways whose
  GatewayClass controllerName matches its own, so the classes coexist; an
  HTTPRoute's backendRefs are independent of its parent Gateway, so both
  route to the identical Services.
end note
@enduml
